{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/escaping-macbook-pro-touchbar","webpackCompilationHash":"b6bef1d996d1ad2e054c","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"b6b5cf9a-eaec-5074-81b3-c77affb611f2","html":"<p>The fact that you have opened this article means that you are already aware of one the biggest problems of Macbook Pro 2016+ models - the <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/macos/touch-bar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">touchbar</a>.</p>\n<p>The touchbar is something Apple have decided to enforce on users as part of their keyboards. It’s not a problem per-se for most users and certainly the bar can serve as a good tool if used properly. The bar becomes a problem for developers, system administrators and all other power users who need a physical key for the <code class=\"language-text\">Esc</code> (escape).</p>\n<p>I personally understand Apple to an extend - how do you force someone to use the touchbar? You force him to NEED to do something with it, otherwise he will continue with old habits.</p>\n<p>I mean, let’s be honest, the trackpad in 2016+ models is HUGE. Realistically, it could be a bit tighter to let the Fn keys and its row just be there with no problems!</p>\n<p>And back to the question of adding an <code class=\"language-text\">Esc</code> key on a physical place you expect and want it to be?</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-add-esc---3-possible-ways\"><a href=\"#how-to-add-esc---3-possible-ways\" aria-label=\"how to add esc   3 possible ways permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to add <code class=\"language-text\">Esc</code> - 3 possible ways</h2>\n<h3 id=\"solution-1-change-modifier-keys\"><a href=\"#solution-1-change-modifier-keys\" aria-label=\"solution 1 change modifier keys permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 1: Change modifier keys</h3>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/c591e/macos-escape-conventional.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 89.98609179415855%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/01472/macos-escape-conventional.webp 240w,\n/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/222bd/macos-escape-conventional.webp 480w,\n/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/620b9/macos-escape-conventional.webp 960w,\n/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/f94f8/macos-escape-conventional.webp 1438w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/0783d/macos-escape-conventional.png 240w,\n/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/782f4/macos-escape-conventional.png 480w,\n/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/f570d/macos-escape-conventional.png 960w,\n/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/c591e/macos-escape-conventional.png 1438w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/4fb91a3a236b53d2edd1e1b6bccc0410/f570d/macos-escape-conventional.png\"\n          alt=\"Adding escape key in MacOS by conventional means\"\n          title=\"Adding escape key in MacOS by conventional means\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>It’s the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/kb/PH25240?locale=en_IE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">official solution</a> which you’ll find first on Google. No problems with it as long as you’re ok to let go of the <code class=\"language-text\">Caps Lock</code>. Who needs it anyway, they said?</p>\n<h3 id=\"solution-2-find-software-to-map-keys\"><a href=\"#solution-2-find-software-to-map-keys\" aria-label=\"solution 2 find software to map keys permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 2: Find software to map keys</h3>\n<p>Natural reflex to find an app which extends on an existing system API. Appears that at some point of time, quite <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/library/content/technotes/tn2450/_index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/DTS40017618-CH1-KEY_TABLE_USAGES\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">important changes</a> happened and that’s why you’ll see controversial opinions on <a href=\"https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Karabiner</a> “before and after”.</p>\n<p>So, apart from the app under question, you can go advanced with <a href=\"https://www.boastr.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">BetterTouchTool</a> and similar premium solutions.</p>\n<p>In short, there are apps on the market - you can spend time searching and trying and evaluating how much it worths spending money on mapping a key or two if that is your goal …</p>\n<h3 id=\"solution-3-go-low-level\"><a href=\"#solution-3-go-low-level\" aria-label=\"solution 3 go low level permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Solution 3: Go low-level</h3>\n<p>There’s <a href=\"http://www.manpagez.com/man/1/hidutil/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">hidutil</a> and the IOKit HID APIs. Probably there are more, these are the initial options I came upon reading the technical note mentioned earlier. You get the idea here - you do it lightly and your way on the experimentation path.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-worked-for-me\"><a href=\"#what-worked-for-me\" aria-label=\"what worked for me permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What worked for me</h2>\n<p>To save you time, I’m giving you this right away: <a href=\"https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Karabiner</a>.</p>\n<p>Basically, my scenario was trickier than standard keyboards because on the left of 1 I have the key for new paragraph (ISO) and not the tilde (ANSI). The discussion in <a href=\"https://github.com/tekezo/Karabiner-Elements/issues/931\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this issue</a> could already be a hint for you what we’re going to do.</p>\n<p>Select to the right layout of keyboard:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/2a380/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.09639727361246%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/01472/macos-escape-set-keyboard.webp 240w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/222bd/macos-escape-set-keyboard.webp 480w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/620b9/macos-escape-set-keyboard.webp 960w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/28063/macos-escape-set-keyboard.webp 1440w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/34ef4/macos-escape-set-keyboard.webp 1920w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/8eb96/macos-escape-set-keyboard.webp 2054w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/0783d/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png 240w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/782f4/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png 480w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/f570d/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png 960w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/8d0ff/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png 1440w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/a987b/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png 1920w,\n/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/2a380/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png 2054w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/7669e7a58bb41631313d641f77671081/f570d/macos-escape-set-keyboard.png\"\n          alt=\"Setting up the keyboard\"\n          title=\"Setting up the keyboard\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In my case, I had to select <code class=\"language-text\">ANSI</code> instead of <code class=\"language-text\">ISO</code>, even though the actual hardware keyboard is <code class=\"language-text\">ISO</code>. If you are honest here, as soon as you map the <code class=\"language-text\">Esc</code> on the <code class=\"language-text\">non_us_backslack</code>, your new paragraph key will go on the tilde … Not cool. Just as in the issue on github.</p>\n<p>Then, just do the mapping as you would do if you didn’t know about any of the possible edge cases described above ;)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/77a98/macos-escape-set-mapping.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.9423076923077%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/01472/macos-escape-set-mapping.webp 240w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/222bd/macos-escape-set-mapping.webp 480w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/620b9/macos-escape-set-mapping.webp 960w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/28063/macos-escape-set-mapping.webp 1440w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/34ef4/macos-escape-set-mapping.webp 1920w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/00f6b/macos-escape-set-mapping.webp 2080w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/0783d/macos-escape-set-mapping.png 240w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/782f4/macos-escape-set-mapping.png 480w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/f570d/macos-escape-set-mapping.png 960w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/8d0ff/macos-escape-set-mapping.png 1440w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/a987b/macos-escape-set-mapping.png 1920w,\n/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/77a98/macos-escape-set-mapping.png 2080w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/fcfbb2d14597a048e3cd6fc9dfdc9815/f570d/macos-escape-set-mapping.png\"\n          alt=\"Setting up the mapping for escape key in MacOS\"\n          title=\"Setting up the mapping for escape key in MacOS\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>And that’s it! Now that physical key next to the fancy touchbar will be your <code class=\"language-text\">Esc</code> as normal :)</p>","fields":{"slug":"escaping-macbook-pro-touchbar","tagSlugs":["/tag/macbook/","/tag/mac-os/","/tag/productivity/","/tag/keyboard/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2018-01-11T23:00:00+01:00","description":"MBP keyboards can cause nightmares!","tags":["Macbook","MacOS","Productivity","Keyboard"],"title":"Escape button in Macbook Pro without using toucbar","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"escaping-macbook-pro-touchbar"}}}